<section
    class="article-section "
   id="s4-7-7"
  
  
>

    <header class="article-section__header">
      <h4 class="article-section__header_text">Decoupling of spatial frequencies</h4>
      
        <a href="https://bio-protocol.org/eLIFErap34560?item=s4-7-7" class="article-section__header_link">Request a detailed protocol</a>
    </header>

  <div class="article-section__body">
      <p class="paragraph">The convolutions in <a href="#equ34">Equations 34 and 60</a> show how the excitatory and inhibitory weight perturbations at one location influence the time evolution of weights at every other location. Transforming the system to frequency space leads to a drastic simplification: The time evolution of a perturbation of a particular spatial frequency depends onlyon the excitatory and inhibitory perturbation of the same spatial frequency, thatis, the Fourier components decouple. We define the Fourier transform <math id="inf152"><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo></mo><mrow><mi class="ltx_font_mathcaligraphic"></mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">[</mo><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi></mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo stretchy="false">]</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow></math> with wavevector <math id="inf153"><mi>k</mi></math> of a function <math id="inf154"><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi></mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow></math> of location <math id="inf155"><mi></mi></math> as:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ61">

    <span class="math-block__label">(61)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mrow><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mo></mo><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop="true" symmetric="true"></mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msubsup><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi></mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo></mo><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo></mo><mi>k</mi><mo></mo><mi></mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mpadded><mo></mo><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mo></mo><mi></mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">and note that</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ62">

    <span class="math-block__label">(62)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mrow><mrow><mrow><msubsup><mo largeop="true" symmetric="true"></mo><mrow><mo>-</mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msubsup><mrow><mpadded width="+1.7pt"><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo>-</mo><mrow><mi>i</mi><mo></mo><mi>k</mi><mo></mo><mi></mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mpadded><mo></mo><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mo></mo><mi></mi></mrow></mrow><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo></mo><mi></mi><mo></mo><mi></mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo rspace="4.2pt" stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow></mrow><mo>.</mo></mrow></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">Using the Convolution theorem and the linearity of the Fourier transform we get</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ63">

    <span class="math-block__label">(63)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mtable columnalign="left" columnspacing="1em" rowspacing="4pt"><mtr><mtd><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msub></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><msubsup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msubsup></mfrac><mo></mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msub></mrow><mi>L</mi></mfrac></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msub></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn><mi></mi><mi></mi><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mo></mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><msubsup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msubsup><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>+</mo><mrow><mo>[</mo><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo>]</mo></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">and</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ64">

    <span class="math-block__label">(64)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mi>t</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mo>.</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">The <math id="inf156"><mrow><mi></mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow></math> term in <a href="#equ63">Equation 63</a> balances homogeneous perturbations in such a way that the output neuron would still fire at the target rate, if not for permutations at other frequencies. In the following, we drop this term, because we are not interested in spatially homogeneous perturbations. Moreover, the continuum limit is validonly for high densities: <math id="inf157"><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></msub><mo>/</mo><mi>L</mi></mrow><mo></mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></math>. We can thus drop terms of lower order than <math id="inf158"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mrow><mo>/</mo></mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow></mstyle></math>, which eliminates the <math id="inf159"><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub><mo></mo><msub><mi></mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo></mo><msub><mi>M</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub></mrow><mrow><msubsup><mi>w</mi><mn>0</mn><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msubsup><mo></mo><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math> term. Writing the remaining terms of <a href="#equ63">Equations 63 and 64</a> as a matrix leads to:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ65">

    <span class="math-block__label">(65)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mrow><mo>[</mo><mtable columnspacing="1em" rowspacing="4pt"><mtr><mtd><mrow><mover><mrow><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mrow><mo></mo></mover></mrow></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mrow><mover><mrow><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mrow><mo></mo></mover></mrow></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mrow><mo>[</mo><mtable columnspacing="1em" rowspacing="4pt"><mtr><mtd><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mtd><mtd><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mtd><mtd><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo>]</mo></mrow><mrow><mo>[</mo><mtable columnspacing="1em" rowspacing="4pt"><mtr><mtd><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mi></mi><msup><mi>w</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mtd></mtr></mtable><mo>]</mo></mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>,</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">which nolongercontains terms from the weight normalization. The characteristic polynomial of the above matrix is:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ66">

    

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi></mi><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">The difference, <math id="inf160"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup></mrow></mstyle></math>, vanishes for Gaussian input, because:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ67">

    <span class="math-block__label">(67)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi></mi><mo>,</mo><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow><mi>L</mi></mfrac><msub><mrow><mo></mo><mrow><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi></mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo></mo></mrow><mi>x</mi></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<div class="math-block" id="equ68">

    <span class="math-block__label">(68)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup></mrow></msub><mrow><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msup></mrow></msub></mrow></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mrow><msubsup><mo></mo><mrow><mo></mo><mrow><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>/</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mrow><mi>L</mi><mrow><mo>/</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mrow></msubsup></mrow><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi></mrow><mi>x</mi><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><mfrac><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo></mo><mi></mi><msup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mfrac><mo></mo><mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<div class="math-block" id="equ69">

    <span class="math-block__label">(69)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mo></mo><mfrac><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><msub><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow></msub><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msup><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow></msub></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi></mi></mrow><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mfrac></mrow></mfrac></msqrt><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><mfrac><msup><mi></mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mfrac></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mo>,</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">where we completed the square and used <math id="inf161"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msubsup><mo></mo><mrow><mo></mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></mrow></msubsup><msup><mi>e</mi><mrow><mo></mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mi></mi><mi>a</mi></mfrac></msqrt></mrow></mstyle></math>. Taking the Fourier transform and completing the square again gives</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ70">

    <span class="math-block__label">(70)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msup><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow></msub><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub><mtext></mtext><msub><mi>M</mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow></msub></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><mfrac><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>+</mo><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mi mathvariant="normal"></mi></msup></mrow><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mo>.</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">and thus <math id="inf162"><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math>.</p>
<p class="paragraph">For <math id="inf163"><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi><mo></mo></msup></mrow></math>,<a href="#equ70">Equation 70</a> simplifies to:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ71">

    <span class="math-block__label">(71)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mrow><msup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msubsup><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">P</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mo>.</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">This leads to the eigenvalues:</p>
<div class="math-block" id="equ72">

    <span class="math-block__label">(72)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<div class="math-block" id="equ73">

    <span class="math-block__label">(73)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mn>1</mn></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo><mo></mo><msup><mi>K</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></msup><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<div class="math-block" id="equ74">

    <span class="math-block__label">(74)</span>

    <span class="math-block__math"><math><mstyle displaystyle="true" scriptlevel="0"><mrow><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>L</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mfrac><mrow><mo>(</mo><mrow><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msubsup><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow><mo></mo><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><msubsup><mi>M</mi><mrow><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></mrow></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow></msub></mrow><mi>exp</mi><mo></mo><mrow><mo>{</mo><mrow><mo></mo><msup><mi>k</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><msubsup><mi></mi><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msubsup></mrow><mo>}</mo></mrow></mrow><mo>)</mo></mrow><mspace width="thinmathspace"/><mo>,</mo></mrow></mstyle></math></span>

</div>
<p class="paragraph">which are shown in <a href="#fig8">Figure 8a</a>. Perturbations with spatial frequencies for which <math id="inf164"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow></math> is positive will grow. Setting <math id="inf165"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mo></mo><msub><mi></mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo></mo><mrow><mo stretchy="false">(</mo><mi>k</mi><mo stretchy="false">)</mo></mrow></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant="normal">d</mi><mo></mo><mi>k</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></mrow></math> gives the wavevector <math id="inf166"><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math> of the Fourier component that grows fastest:</p>
