              <figcaption class="captioned-asset__caption">
          
                  <h6 class="caption-text__heading">Results of the mathematical analysis.</h6>
                
                
                <div class="caption-text__body"><p class="paragraph">(<b>a</b>) The eigenvalue spectrum for the eigenvalues of <a href="#equ72">Equation 72</a> for an excitatory tuning of width <math id="inf167"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0.03</mn></mrow></math>. The first eigenvalue <math id="inf168"><msub><mi></mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> is always 0. If the inhibitory tuning is more narrow than the excitatory tuning, thatis, <math id="inf169"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub></mrow></math>, the second eigenvalue <math id="inf170"><msub><mi></mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is negative for every wavevector <math id="inf171"><mi>k</mi></math>. For <math id="inf172"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub></mrow></math> the eigenvalue spectrum has a unique positive maximum <math id="inf173"><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math>, thatis, a most unstable spatial frequency. The wavevector <math id="inf174"><msub><mi>k</mi><mi>max</mi></msub></math> at which <math id="inf175"><msub><mi></mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> is maximal is obtained from <a href="#equ78">Equation 78</a> and marked with a dashed line. (<b>b</b>) The dependence of the grid spacing on learning rate <math id="inf176"><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub></math>, number of input neurons <math id="inf177"><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub></math> and input height <math id="inf178"><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub></math> is accurately predicted by the theory. The gray line shows the grid spacing obtained from <a href="#equ78">Equation 78</a>. We vary the inhibitory learning rate, <math id="inf179"><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub></math> (circles), the number of inhibitory input neurons, <math id="inf180"><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub></math> (squares), or the square of the height of the inhibitory input place fields, <math id="inf181"><msubsup><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math> (diamonds). The horizontal axis shows the ratio of the product <math id="inf182"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo></mo><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo></mo><msubsup><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></mrow></math> to the initial value of the product <math id="inf183"><msub><mi></mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math>. We keep <math id="inf184"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>0.3</mn><mo></mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></math>, <math id="inf185"><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>800</mn></mrow></math> and <math id="inf186"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">E</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></math> in each simulation and the <math id="inf187"><msub><mi></mi><mn>0</mn></msub></math> parameters are: <math id="inf188"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mrow><mn>0.3</mn><mo></mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mrow></math>, <math id="inf189"><mrow><msub><mi>N</mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>200</mn></mrow></math>, <math id="inf190"><mrow><msub><mi></mi><mi mathvariant="normal">I</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></math>. (<b>c</b>) Distribution of minimal values of GRF input. Histograms show the distribution of the minimal values of 1000 Gaussian random fields for a small linear track, <math id="inf191"><mrow><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></math>, and a large linear track <math id="inf192"><mrow><mi>L</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1000</mn></mrow></math>. Red and blue colors correspond to the tuning of excitatory and inhibitory input neurons, respectively. Each dotted line indicates the mean of the histogram of the same color. For larger systems, the distribution of the minimum values gets more narrow and the relative distance between the minima of excitatory and inhibitory neurons decreases.</p>
</div>
          
